âœ… 1. Capture Full Page Screenshot

await page.goto('https://example.com');

await page.screenshot({ path: 'screenshots/fullpage.png', fullPage: true });
ğŸ“¸ Captures the entire scrollable page, not just the visible viewport.

âœ… 2. Capture Visible Viewport Only (Default)

await page.screenshot({ path: 'screenshots/viewport.png' });
ğŸ” Useful if you only care about what's currently visible.

âœ… 3. Capture Screenshot of a Specific Element

const logo = page.locator('#logo');
await logo.screenshot({ path: 'screenshots/logo.png' });
ğŸ¯ Use when you only want to snapshot a button, form, or chart.

âœ… 4. Take Screenshot on Assertion Failure (Debug)

try {
  await expect(page.locator('h1')).toHaveText('Dashboard');
} catch (error) {
  await page.screenshot({ path: 'screenshots/error.png', fullPage: true });
  throw error;
}
âœ… 5. Automatically Capture Screenshots on Test Failure (Playwright Test Runner)
In playwright.config.js:
use: {
  screenshot: 'only-on-failure', // or 'on', 'off'
}
ğŸ“‚ Screenshots will be saved automatically in the test output directory.

âœ… 6. Timestamped or Dynamic Filenames

const timestamp = new Date().toISOString().replace(/[:.]/g, '-');
await page.screenshot({ path: `screenshots/home-${timestamp}.png`, fullPage: true });
âœ… 7. Compare Screenshots (Visual Testing)
Use Playwrightâ€™s toMatchSnapshot() for visual diffing:

await expect(page).toHaveScreenshot(); // Compares with baseline
